## CSS CONVENTIONS

All colors are defined as CSS custom properties on `:root`. Always use these variables:

```css
--grass: #1a4a2e        /* dark green */
--grass-light: #2d6b45  /* medium green */
--dirt: #c4874a         /* orange/tan */
--chalk: #f5f0e8        /* off-white text */
--cream: #faf7f2        /* lightest background tone */
--gold: #d4a843         /* primary accent */
--gold-dark: #b8892a    /* gold hover state */
--red: #c0392b          /* error/danger */
--red-light: #e74c3c    /* lighter red */
--navy: #0d1b2a         /* main background */
--navy-mid: #1a2e42     /* secondary background */
--sky: #3a7bd5          /* blue accent (rarely used) */
--score-good: #27ae60   /* green score color */
--score-ok: #f39c12     /* yellow score color */
--score-bad: #c0392b    /* red score color */
```

Never use hardcoded hex values for colors that already have a variable.

