## SCRIPTS/UPDATE_STATS.PY

- Uses only the standard library + `requests` — do not add other dependencies
- Hits `https://statsapi.mlb.com/api/v1` — no API key required, be polite with `time.sleep(0.3)` between requests
- Only updates players where `"active": true`
- Writes back to `players.json` in place
- Exits with code 1 if more than 20% of active players fail to update (signals a broken API)
- The GitHub Action will only commit if `players.json` actually changed

